result.execSummary:
The defendant Cathleen R. Seace was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

charges.dispoDesc: Guilty Due to No Contest Plea

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Cathleen R. Seace

records.addlTxt:
10:10 AM Defendant Cathleen R. Seace appeared in court. Karl J. Kelz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint acknowledged, reading waived.  Notice of right to attorney given to DE.  Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled.  DE enters plea of NO CONTEST to all counts. Off record until initial appearances are finished. Back on record at 10:30 AM. Appearances are as previously stated. Defendant wishes to proceed with the No Contest plea entered earlier.   Defendant freely, voluntarily, and intelligently waives right to attorney. Court questions DE regarding the plea. DA explains elements of charge and gives sentencing recommendations. Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders entry of JOC. Comments by parties.
Court Imposes:
$250 Fine
$200 DNA + Sample 

Payment plan granted: $100/mo. Starting on or before 05/17/2022 intil paid in full OR one day in jail for every $25 not paid. 

Appeal Rights Given
Demand for discovery and Notice of Intent to use DNA
